HEADWORD: Jambeux
<hw>Jam"beux</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[From F. <ets>jambe</ets> a leg: cf. OF.
<ets>jambiere</ets>. See <er>Jamb</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<fld>(Ancient Armor)</fld> <def>In the Middle Ages, armor for the legs
below the knees, usually having front and back pieces; called also
<altname>greaves</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>giambeux</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
